			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Disabling the PPU for good (both sprites and BG) has the annoying side effect of corrupting OAM (this was discovered by tepples a while ago) unless you obey some mystical conditions (like the exact point in the scanline where you do it or which sprites are visible in that scanline).</div><br />Mystical nothing. It takes 64 dots to start the sprite evaluator each line, 128 to check whether all are in range, and 6 more for each that is in range. If all 8 are in range, that's 240 dots, so if you can turn it off between 240 and 255 you're golden.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

