					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I don't understand why people would be bothered by glitches on the background, but not on the sprites.<br /><br />Attributes clashes on a scrolling BG are also &quot;so brief&quot; and &quot;near the edge of the screen&quot;, yet people seems to find them unacceptable.<br /><br />That being said I perfectly respect that you'd make such a choice, I was just pointing out that if you aim for perfect scrolling, sprites should be taken into consideration, too, because yes, this is noticeable, and probably moreso than 3 pixel attributes clashes on a horizontal scrolling BG using horizontal mirroring such as in my demo.</div>

