					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">[Off topic post.] Sprites 1. Show up 100% and correctly. 2. Aren't clearly visible for lots of frames. 3. Can be eliminated by game design ad not having enemies come from the top?<br /><br />But still, if you use CHR-RAM for the 4 screen, you'll be giving up lots of space in the RAM. But it's not too bad. Stick a 16KB RAM on there and have at it, I guess?<br /><br />But still, IMO, software patching and making the screen off-center just to fix it are worse design choices than giving up a tiny bit of your profit. If you're not using custom boards, then software is the best way. But if you can develop a PCB, then just stick a 4KB RAM in a devtendo and start going at it. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

